    <stitle>ELECTRICAL SYSTEM TROUBLESHOOTING GUIDE - 9800 - CAB - TILT: 9600 AND 9700 SLEEPER AND NON-SLEEPER CABS -
        CAB TILTING PROCEDURE - CAB TILT HYDRAULIC SYSTEM
    </stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="describe" graphiccount="1">
        <title>CAB TILT HYDRAULIC SYSTEM</title>
        <para>The cab tilt hydraulic system (
            <hotlnk xrefid="f1600621">Figure 21</hotlnk>) uses two hydraulic lift cylinders or rams which are actuated
            by the hydraulic lift pump which can be either manual or air powered. (This pump also provides the hydraulic
            pressure for the automatic release of cab latch hook.)
        </para>
