        <para>A minimum of maintenance is required for keeping the cab mounting/tilting system in order. It consists
            mainly of keeping lift pump reservoir filled with correct hydraulic fluid Dexron Automatic Transmission
            Fluid (ATF) at all times.
            <emph type="bold">Do not use BRAKE FLUID.</emph>
        </para>
        <para>Inspect system regularly to be sure plumbing is free from damage or leaks. If the system operates poorly
            or fails to operate, repair or replace component(s) as necessary.
        </para>
        <para>Also, lubricate latch hook pivot points periodically and when the vehicle is due for regular maintenance,
            use engine oil or an anti-seize lubricant.
        </para>
        <specpara>
            <note>
                <para>The cab tilt hydraulic system (cylinder, lift rams, lift pump, valves, fluid lines, etc.) will
                    perform more efficiently if operated periodically. Do not allow system to stand idle for long
                    periods (over 60 days).
                </para>
            </note>
        </specpara>
        <specpara>
            <note>
                <para>If the cab has to be raised mechanically, refer to
                    <hotlnk document="s16006_11.xml" xrefid="hl1600603">LIFT CAB MECHANICALLY
                        <xref refid="hl1600603"/>
                    </hotlnk>
                    .
                </para>
            </note>
        </specpara>
